<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  CLAUDE CLI HEALTH CANARY — installed 2026-06-22; relocated to internal disk 2026-06-24.

  Proactive early-warning probe for the failure modes that silently break EVERY
  headless `claude --print` launchd job at once:
    1. AUTH (primary)  — stale Claude CLI OAuth token / out of credits (401).
                         Human-only fix: `claude login`. Tested via the real
                         claude binary, so it is high-confidence.
    2. VAULT (proxy)   — a scheduled job can't read the INTERNAL-disk vault
                         (broad FDA revocation for background jobs).
    3. MOUNT (the one  — a scheduled job can't READ /Volumes/AI_Workspace (EPERM).
       that mattered)    THIS is the failure that went 16h SILENT on 2026-06-23: a
                         `brew upgrade claude-code` re-symlinks the binary and
                         invalidates the external volume's FDA grant.

  ⚠️ RUNS THE INTERNAL-DISK COPY: ~/iris_studio/scripts/auth_canary.sh, NOT the
  repo copy on the mount. The 6/23 outage proved the original on-mount design
  circular — when AI_Workspace lost FDA, launchd couldn't read the script, so it
  never ran and never alerted. The internal-disk copy + the script's Keychain
  alert fallback let the canary survive the exact outage it detects. The repo copy
  (scripts/auth_canary.sh) is the SOURCE OF TRUTH; redeploy after editing it:
    cp scripts/auth_canary.sh ~/iris_studio/scripts/auth_canary.sh

  Fires ONE purpose-built Telegram alert on a healthy→broken transition, a
  throttled re-ping while still broken, and a single ✅ on recovery. Silent when
  healthy. Named with the `claude-code-` prefix so it lists alongside the other
  jobs in `launchctl list | grep claude-code`.

  Schedule: every 3h (StartInterval 10800) + RunAtLoad so it self-tests the
  moment it is (re)loaded. One tiny `claude --print` per run — negligible quota.

  Manage:
    launchctl bootout gui/$(id -u)/com.iris.claude-code-auth-canary 2>/dev/null
    cp scripts/com.iris.claude-code-auth-canary.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
    launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.iris.claude-code-auth-canary.plist
    launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.iris.claude-code-auth-canary   # test fire
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>Label</key>
	<string>com.iris.claude-code-auth-canary</string>
	<key>ProgramArguments</key>
	<array>
		<string>/bin/bash</string>
		<string>-lc</string>
		<string>/Users/steve/iris_studio/scripts/auth_canary.sh</string>
	</array>
	<key>RunAtLoad</key>
	<true/>
	<key>StandardErrorPath</key>
	<string>/Users/steve/iris_studio/logs/auth-canary.stderr.log</string>
	<key>StandardOutPath</key>
	<string>/Users/steve/iris_studio/logs/auth-canary.stdout.log</string>
	<key>StartInterval</key>
	<integer>10800</integer>
</dict>
</plist>
